1 DEATH~
When your character dies, your spirit rises from your body and hovers
over your corpse.  A new body will be rushed to you as soon as one can be
assigned.  In the meantime, since you have no physical presence, you can't
do much.  You can see what goes on in the room, but you can't do anything
about it.  When your new body arrives, you will be reincarnated in the same
room where you died.  You may then get your stuff back from your corpse,
that is if others haven't gotten there first.  Your new body will be
temporarily invulnerable and will have enough sight to get your stuff even
in a darkened room.  You may then recall to begin healing if you like.  You
do lose experience when you are killed by a mobile, approximately one half
level's worth.  When you are killed by another player, your experience is
unaffected, but your equipment will likely not be so lucky!  
~

1 EXPERIENCE LEVEL XP~
Your character advances in power by gaining experience.  You need so much
experience per level based on your race and your class, and also your level.
As you gain in levels so does your experience per level gain.
{x
You gain experience by: being part of a group that kills a monster
{x                        being rewarded for excellent roleplaying
{x                        per-tick experience
{x                        improving skills (minor gains only)
{x
You lose experience by: fleeing from a battle 
{x                        dying by the hands of a mob
{x
The experience you get from a kill depends on several things:
- how many players are in your group;
- your level versus the level of the monster;
- your alignment versus the monster's alignment.
{x
Experience for roleplaying depends on the situation.  Always make a
point of displaying your best roleplaying abilities.  Immortals will
often reward excellent roleplayers when a player least expects it.
Per-Tick Experience is awarded to ALL Classes, but more for Blacksmiths. This
feature allows people who prefer to play a class that does not participate
in combat, the chance to gain Experience Points.  The gains will begin
after the player has been logged in for a particular amount of time, and
then will continue every tick there after. This experience is not as
effective as combat experience, but is intended to allow players to have
characters with pacifistic characters if they so choose.  Do *not* abuse
this feature.  It is intended to reward and make possible certain character
concepts.  Remaining idle for prolonged periods of time using triggers and
such in order to abuse this feature is unacceptable.
~

