1 KNIGHT~
The chivalrous Knights are experts in combat.  Skilled in most forms of
battle, Knights differ from warriors in that they are more disciplined and
must follow the strict rules of their order.  Knights also tend to be very
religious and it is from their religious beliefs that they gain some of
their and abilities.  No matter his cause, be it for good or evil; in
defense or defiance of law, the knight is a universal symbol of
guardianship, has an unbending will of an absolute ruler, and the
destructive force of a mighty siege engine.  The knight stands for all of
this in the name of his duty.  Those enjoying his protection live their
lives in peace, while those who seek to subvert it find themselves scaling
sheer battlements as they struggle beneath the boiling blood of the knight's
determination.  There are knights, of course, whose bastions have been
crushed, or who have lost sight of their purpose, and these are tragic
souls...  But they are still not to be crossed.  Often times, despair and
distrust wield swords far more powerful than those of belief and idealism. 
The Knight is a master of heavy arms, just as skilled at sheathing himself
in steel as he is at sheathing steel in his enemies.  His abilities reflect
the tremendous strength that allows him to move freely in armor that would
break an ordinary man, as well as the indomitable will that forged him into
the deadliest of weapons.  
~

