0 solamnic~
{WFor a detailed help on each order type: HELP KNIGHT CROWN, HELP KNIGHT
SWORD, HELP KNIGHT ROSE.  {x 
 
HISTORY
The Knights of Solamnia arose in the Age of Dreams, about three millennia 
before the War of the Lance. The order was founded the commander of the 
Ergothian Palace Guard, Vinas Solamnus. Sent by his Emperor to quell a 
rebellion in northeastern Ergoth, Vinas saw instead that the rebellion was 
justified. 
 
During the Third Dragon War, a young knight of the Crown became a legend
and the most enduring symbol of Solamnic Honor and sacrifice when he and
the silver dragon known as Heart receive the first Dragonlance and sacrifice
themselves to banish Takhisis and her evil dragons from the world.
To this day, the knight known as Huma Dragonbane is revered and celebrated
as the Knighthood's greatest hero.
 
Blamed unjustly for the Cataclysm, the Knighthood was reviled during the
Age of Despair and many knights abandoned their sacred oaths. A courageous
few remained steadfast to their code and the Knighthood gained respect and
power during the War of the Lance. Having once forgotten the spirit of the
Oath in favor of the unfeeling letter of the Measure, it took a noble act
of sacrifice by another young man named Sturm Brightblade to remind the
Knighthood that honor lies in the heart of each knight, not in a set of
dusty books.
 
For countless generations, the Knights of Solamnia were drawn only from
Solamnic nobility,  and often with families tied very close to the Knighthood.
During and after the War of the Lance, however, the knights opened their
ranks to non-Solamnics and allowed those not of noble blood to ascend to
their highest ranks.
 
THE OATH AND THE MEASURE
All knights are bound by the Oath "Est Sularus oth Mithas", meaning "My honor
is my life". A knight's actions throughout life are defined by an extensive
code of laws known as the Measure.
 
The Oath and the Measure provide the knight courage in the face of terrible
danger, give the knight strength when the knight's own is failing, and
grant the knight guidance when confronted with difficult choices. The Oath
and the Measure lead a knight to champion the cause of Good and uphold the
laws (at least those that are consistant with his beliefs). An honorable
knight helps those in need, without expecting or requesting a reward.
 
REQUIREMENTS:
All those wishing to join the SOLAMNIC order must meet the following:
 
ALIGNMENT - All prospective members must be of Lawful or Neutral ethos, with
Lawful being strongly preferred. Alignment must be Good; those who change or
do not maintain this alignment will be removed if discovered.
 
RELIGION: While the knighthood reveres all gods of Good, all squires and
knights are expected to remain devoted to one of the three patron gods of
the knighthood: Paladine, Kiri-Jolith, or Habbakuk.
 
RACE RESTRICTIONS:
Traditionally, the knights have allowed only humans to join their ranks,
though after the War of the Lance they began to accept half-elves among
their numbers. Exceptional individuals of other races /may/ be considered for
knighthood, however most are instead encouraged to serve in the Solamnic
Auxillary - a volunteer reserve unit overseen by the Order of the Sword.
 
ACCEPTED CLASSES: Knights, Warriors, Barbarians, Clerics, and Battlemages
are currently the only classes considered eligible for full knighthood.
 
Those wishing to join may send a note to SOLAMNIC, or contact a Lord Knight
to arrange an interview.
~

1 'KNIGHT TAKHISIS' KOT~
{DThe Knights of Takhisis{x

 The Knights of Takhisis are a military Order created for, and dedicated
to, a single cause, the total and unquestioned domination of Krynn in the
name of Her Dark Majesty, Queen Takhisis.  
 
Lord Ariakan, the purported son of Dragon Highlord Ariakas and the goddess
Zeboim, founded the Knights of Takhisis after spending six years as a prisoner
of the Knights of Solamnia, during which time he learned all he could from
them; the strengths and weaknesses of their Measure and the value in their
system of honor and discipline.
 
Ariakan maintained that the keys to victory are order, discipline, and vision:
"Bring order to our followers, and they will accomplish. Discipline them, and
they will achieve. Give them vision, and they will move forward toward a common
goal". In accordance with this, Ariakan created the foundations of the Knights
of Takhisis - the Vision, the Blood Oath, and the Code.
 
For organizational structure, see 'HELP KOT2'
For membership information and restrictions, see 'HELP KOT JOIN'
For ranking structure, see 'HELP KOT RANKS'
For information on each Order, see 'HELP KNIGHT LILY', 'HELP KNIGHT SKULL', and
'HELP KNIGHT THORN'
