0 RANGER~
Rangers are the vanguard of civilization.  They seek to subdue nature, to
blunt its harmful energies while protecting it from the ravages of
civilization.  Rangers are instrumental in charting new paths and roads
through great forests, discovering new mountain passes, and delving into the
great wastelands to find lost wonders and forgotten dangers.  These
explorers are at home in the wild, able to cook their own game and to build
campsites to live in nature.  Rangers possess many skills of the martial
arts which are unknown to city-trained warriors.  
~

0 'DRUID'~
Druids are the bane of civilization.  They seek to unleash nature, to
turn aside the devouring tide of cities, farms, and roads before they
destroy all the glories of nature; to this end they have conjured up strange
and terrible forces of creation, which give them mysterious and fearsome
magical powers.  Druids sometimes organize themselves into circles or
covens, commanding weird rituals of sacrifice in darkened forest glades.  It
is they who ensure that many lone travellers do not re-emerge from the
wilderness.  
~

102 NOTITLE~
Syntax: NOTITLE <player>

This command will toggle(change) the player's ability to have a "Special"
strung title.  All players, when created, start out with a PLR flag called
NOTITLE.  With this flag on, each time they level, they shall recieve a
pre-set title defined within our code structure.  Now, if someone has
roleplayed well, and an Immortal believes he or she should be awarded a
special title, then you must turn their NOTITLE flag off.  Typing in this
command followed by the player's name is all you need to do.  Only type it
in once.  Once you have removed their NOTITLE flag, you will then be able to
STRING a new title for them.  Once a new title is strung, DO NOT re-NOTITLE
them again.  This is a toggle command.  If you type it in again, after you
turned it off and gave them a special title, as soon as they level up,
they'll lose it.  So, once you take the flag off and string them that
special title, do nothing else.  With their special title, and the NOTITLE
flag OFF, they will continue to level throughout their remaining levels WITH
the special title.  This is as "Barney" as I can get.  If you have any
questions, first off, your dumb.  Second, please ask an Implimentor to help
you out.  
~

