1 CHARGE~
Syntax: Charge <victim> <murder|theft|assault|treason|outlaw>
{x        charge <character> <check>
 
Charge will bring up charges against a person if found guilty. What this
will do is FLAG a person, either with KILLER, THIEF, ASSAULT, TREASON, or
OUTLAW flags. Multiple charges can be brought up on someone who's found
guilty of all their crimes. This command may ONLY be used by members of
the Solamnic clan (reason being that they were the only ones who "policed"
the world of Krynn). Do not get out of hand flagging people. Do not FLAG
people just because you do not like someone, or because they did something
to one of your Alt characters. If this command gets out of hand, it shall
be removed. This command gives players a chance at governing the world
themselves a little. Charges may only be brought up on someone properly
convicted. An example would be something like this:
 
Player 1 attacks player 2.
Player 1 has to flee, and fails at murdering player 2.
Player 2 runs to find a Solamnic in the area.
Player 2 gives the whole run down of what happened and even has witnesses.
The Solamnic takes in all the evidence, but must first get player 1's side
of the story.
Player 1 says he didn't attack player 2, that it was the other way around.
Player 1 doesn't have any witnesses though.
Solamnic feels that Player 1 is guilty, so he CHARGES player 1 with ASSAULT.
 
Now, yes, there will be lying and people getting flagged for crimes they
did not commit. It would be much easier for any Solamnic to not charge
anyone with any crime, unless they witnessed it themselves, or were in the
same area and heard Player 2 YELL that he was being attacked by Player 1.
Reason being, is that if someone is wrongly accused of a crime, and is
flagged for it, they just might seek out retribution on you, the Solamnic.
 
The flags should be used for crimes as follows:
 
Murder  - Given to someone only if they're successful at killing their victim.
Theft   - Given to someone who tries to steal from someone and is caught.
Assault - Someone simply ATTACKS someone, but does NOT succeed in killing them.
Treason - Can only be given to fellow Solamnic clan memebers, for doing
          something against Solamnic Rules set forth by the leaders.
          (An example of this would be a Solamnic attacking another Solamnic,
          or a Solamnic secretly helping out a sworn enemy of the Solamnic
          knighthood and is caught)
Outlaw  - Give to anyone who abandons (quits) their Clan without permission
          from the clan's leader. (If a leader of any other CLAN wishes
          to bring one of their clanmates up on this charge, they must first
          find a solamnic knight, and then prove to them that they are the
          leader of their clan first.
 
If in doubt, always ask an Immortal for advice as to what to do in any
situation you can't reach a decision on.
 
 
Using CHECK as the third argument, shows the player's RAP SHEET. For
every crime they've ever committed, how many times charged for
that crime, and how many times pardoned for each crime as well. This will
aid in making decisions when CHARGING someone with a crime. You can see
if they are habitual criminals or not.
~

