102 MEMCHECK~
Basically, this WIZNET feature helps track down memory leaks.  This new
wiznet feature can be annoying, in that it's always going to show up, the
more players typing in commands, the more spam messages.  So you might not
want to have this on, unless that's all your doing, is locating memory
leaks.  Basically it compares the number of allocated strings and perm
blocks after a command is executed to the number prior to execution and if
there has been an increase flags this on a new wiznet channel.  Now, the
observant among you will notice that this will flag a hell of a lot of olc
commands which by their very nature allocate new memory, plus lots of common
commands which during their execution may need a block of a size currently
not around so it's allocated.  This in mind though, seeing a command that
shouldnt be alocating flagging on wiznet say, 3 times in a row, can be a
pretty darn good indication that maybe there's a leak.  A lot of commands
will be flagged, but if someone types in the same command like 2 or 3 times
in a row, and the flag comes up each time, please send a note to IMMORTAL
about this, with what happened, so we can take a look at it and maybe fix
the leak.  
~

