1 'DISMISS'~
Syntax: dismiss <mob>
 
This command will dismiss a mobile, sending them back to where they came
from. This command requires the mobile victim to be charmed and under your
control for most of the dismissable mobs. The list of mobiles below fall
under this requirement:
 
MAGE SUMMONED MOBS:

- rabbits
- ethereal warriors
- nightmares
- zombies
- skeletons
- unseen servants
- skeleton warriors
- bears (ranger summon using 'bear call' skill)
- squires (balanceorder clan summons, using 'squire call' skill)
 
Some mobs do not neccissarily require them to be charmed. Some require only
that the person doing the dismissing, is of the same clan that the person
who summoned the mob is of. These mobs can be dismissed at any time, even
if the person who is controlling them is still around, and one of his fellow
clan members decides to dimiss them for a laugh (note: NOT recommended). The
list of mobs below fall under these stipulations:
 
CLAN SUMMONED MOBS: (excludes the squire call skill)
 
- Wardens (Solamnic clan backup summon)
- Hounds  (Mercenary clan backup summon)
- Sentries (KOT clan backup summon)
 
NOTE: This command will not work for just any MOB. This command will only work
for those listed above, otherwise it would get way out of hand. The other
reason for that is because there's too many possible combinations for pets
and charmable mobs.
~

1 'ADMIT'~
Syntax: admit <char> <clan name> [ leader ]
 
This command will admit a person into their clan. Only Leaders and Immortals
can admit someone into their clan. Only Immortals can induct a person as a
LEADER into their own clan. Only Implementors can induct Immortals into a
clan, and only Implementors can induct people into other clans not of their
own, as both a member and a leader. In the Syntax above, adding the word
LEADER after the clan name your inducting someone into, will induct that
person into the clan as not only a member of that clan, but also as a leader.
 
See also: Help Evict
~

