102 MPSTAT~
Syntax: mpstat <mobile>
 
This command will show you the Mprog that a mob is currently using. For
example, MPSTAT PROPHET shows you this:
 
Mobile #3084   [A crazed prophet]
Delay   0      [No target]
[No programs set]
 
It's kind of a useless command, because you can check out a mob's Mprog, by
simply going into MEDIT for that mob's VNUM. Type SHOW to see that Mprog
that is set. This command however, helps in that, if you do not have editing
privledges for an area, but want to know what the TRIGGER is on a particular
mob, this command will show you what it is.
~

102 MPDUMP~
Syntax: mpdump <vnum of Mprog>
 
This command kind of works in conjunction with the Mpstat command,
in that, once you have found a MOB with a working Mprog, and you know
the VNUM of the Mprog, Mpdump, will show you the entire Mprog as it is
written. So, if you type MPSTAT TRIFF, you get:
 
Mobile #10890  [Triff Handflute]
Delay   0      [No target]
[ 1] Trigger [ACT     ] Program [10890] Phrase [looks at you.]
 
Now, you know the VNUM for the Mprog, 10890. Typing Mpdump 10890 shows:
 
smile $n
say Nice to meet you but I must get back to work.
shake
say So much work, so little time.
 
As long as you know the VNUM of the Mprog you want to see, this command
will show you as if you were in MPEDIT and typed SHOW.
~

