1 'SET TRAPS'~
Syntax: Drop <trap>

Using this skill, a ranger may set a trap in a wilderness area.  To set a
trap, the ranger must first purchace a trap, and then drop it in the area
where he wishes to have the trap set.  The first person to enter the area
after the trap has been set will suffer the effects of the trap unless they
manage to disarm it with a 'disarm traps' skill.  Traps will have a variety
of effects depending on the kind of trap.  Setting traps does not enable a
ranger to set boobytraps, nor does it make the Ranger immune to his/her own
trap, so make sure not to walk in on your own trap without the 'disarm
traps' skill.  
~

1 BOOBYTRAP~
Syntax: Drop <boobytrap>

Using this skill, a thief may boobytrap the rooms or narrow streets found
within a city.  To set a trap, the thief must first purchace such a trap,
and then drop it in the desired area.  The first person to enter the area
after the trap has been set will suffer the effects of the boobytrap unless
they manage to disarm it with the 'disarm traps' skill.  Traps will have a
variety of effects, depending on the kind of trap.  The knowledge a thief
aquires regarding boobytraps does not enable the thief to set wilderness
traps, nor does it prevent the thief from being immune to his/her own traps
they set, so be careful not to set your own trap off.  
~

