This skill will allow a Blacksmith to take apart a piece of armor, or a
weapon, to use it for raw materials.  Of course, a smith cannot dismantle
something, if they do not know what the object is made of (it has an unknown
material or it is not in the material list) 
~

1 'FORGEDEATH'~
Syntax: c 'forgedeath' <object>
 
This spell forges a deadly edge on the weapon the caster is
wielding. The caster MUST be wielding the weapon intended to be
cast upon. The deadly edge makes the weapon quite more effective
in battle.
~

103 FORCE~
Syntax: force <character> <command>
Syntax: force all <command>

FORCE forces one character to execute a command, except of course delete.
Below level 107 (Deity) force can only be used on mobiles, and force all is
unavailable.  You also cannot 'force orc murder hugo', for example.

FORCE 'all' forces all player characters to execute a command.
This is typically used for 'force all save'. 
~

1 'UNHOLYRITE'~
Syntax: unholyrite

 This skill allows one who works with death to gain one's health through
a sacrifice to the God of Death, Chemosh.  The sacrifice requires a
substantial amount of mental power along with a jar of blood.  The sacrifice
will not be accepted by Chemosh if one is already at full strength.  
~

102 'CHECK'~
Syntax:
'check'         display info about players
'check stats'   display info and resume stats
'check eq'      resume eq of all players
'check process' check processes of the MUD
'check snoop'   check to see who's snooping who
 
Use the stat command in case of doubt about someone...
