1 'BEAUTY' 'BEAUTY RELIGION'~
The followers of Branchala embrace Beauty in all of it's various forms;
be it music, poetry, art or a simple sunset.  Especially valued by Elves and
Kender, this faith celebrates the inner beauty of the soul through melody
and merriment, seeking to bring all of Krynn's population together to
experience the harmony of living.
 
Followers are encouraged to spread music and art throughout the land,
introduce people to the beauty of the written and spoken word, and
bring pleasure to those around them through the appreciation of
beauty in all it's forms; using music and stories both to entertain and
to teach. Bards in particular tend to be among the most notable of
Branchala's worshippers.
 
Followers of Branchala tend to be of Neutral or Good alignment, and
Neutral or Chaotic ethos; being of the opinion that Lawful strictures
are often too constricting to allow true appreciation of all that life
has to offer, and that those rooted in Evil are often the destroyers
of the Beauty that Branchala holds dear.
 
Devotees of Beauty are often called upon to assist in celebrations,
weddings and public performances. Those wishing to be MARK'ed by
Beauty must compose a story, song or poem illustrating the inherent
beauty in life and the natural world. Once Marked by the god, followers
are responsible for mentoring younger devotees, helping to lift the
hearts of those around them through Branchala's message of beauty and
harmony, and using their talents to help those in need.
 
Above all, followers of Branchala adhere to the following guidelines:
 
{x  ** Art is done for it's own sake - Always give your best performance,
{x     no matter the audience.
{x
{x  ** Respect Nature and its beauty - it is the source of life.
{x
{x  ** Always end the day with a good story.
~

1 'WHITEMAGIC' 'WHITE MAGIC' 'WHITEMAGIC RELIGION' 'WHITE MAGIC RELIGION'~
The followers of Solinari work to promote goodness in the world through
the use of White Magic, believing that a world in which good deeds and
thoughts predominate will benefit all races and end suffering. They
believe that magic is a gift to be shared with the world and used for
the benefit of all.
 
Users of White Magic are encouraged to bring other worthy candidates to
the study of the Art, and seek out lost libraries and magical items with
which to expand the use of magic in the world. While followers of Solinari
are opposed to the goals pursued by worshippers of Nuitari, they will
cooperate to ensure the continued safety and existance of the Art.
 
In keeping with the teaching and aims of Solinari, all who would study
White Magic may be of Lawful or Neutral ethos, but MUST be of Good
alignment. Should a White-robed mage stray from these beliefs, he or she
will soon find that they lose the god's blessings. Humans and Elves are
by far the most prolific of Solinari's followers, but by no means exclusive.
 
RESTRICTIONS: Certain Races may be deemed unacceptable to receive the
blessings of Solinari. These generally include:
 
{x  ** Theiwar and Daergar: While dwarven wizards are not unheard of, these
{x     clans in particular are known for their tendancy toward dark magic.
{x  ** Draconians: The very existance of these creatures and the manner of
{x     their creation is an affront to the strictures and ideals of White Magic.
{x  ** Gnomes: Most gnomes exhibit a strong distaste for magic, preferring
{x     to rely on science and technology. While they may be capable of using
{x     magic, few realize they have the potential. Indeed, calling a gnome
{x     a wizard is considered a deadly insult by most.
{x  ** Kender: While Kender are often very interested in the effects of
{x     magic, due to their inherent nature they are unable to maintain the
{x     necessary focus needed to master the magical arts.
 
Other races wishing to receive the blessings of Solinari may do so at
the god's discretion. While recorded instances of sea elves, minotaurs
and others do exist, they are generally so few as to be considered
aberrations.
 
Those followers wishing to receive a MARK of Solinari's favor must often
undertake a quest of some sort involving the search for rare magical
artifacts, the use of magic for some great benefit to others, or the
gathering of "stray" mages into the fold.
 
All mages MARKed by their god are asked to include themselves in the
Conclave of Wizards as a sign of solidarity and dedication to the Art.
Once accepted, White mages are often the first choice for dealing with
Renegade wizards. Followers of White Magic will attempt to bring their
brethren before the Council with a minimum of force, using violence
ONLY as a last resort.
 
The defining guidelines for followers of White Magic are as follows:
 
{x  ** Devote yourself to Magic.
{x
{x  ** Use your magic for the benefit of all.
{x
{x  ** Guard magic against those who would destroy it.
~

