ORGANIZATION OF THE KNIGHTHOOD

{DThe Vision{x
The Vision is - in simple terms - a statement of the ultimate goal of the
knighthood.  For knights of Takhisis, the Vision is embodied in the phrase:
"One World Order."  The goal is no less than the total and unquestioned
domination of the entire world of Krynn.  The Blood Oath and the Code are
established to work toward that end.  
 
{rThe Blood Oath{x
The Blood Oath is simple: "Submit or die." When joining the knighthood, each
knight dedicates body and soul utterly to the cause. All thoughts of self are
submerged, sublimated in the will of the Dark Queen. Yet this does not mean
that knights may not think for themselves; instead, each knight is encouraged
to act in accordance with their own judgement under the guidelines of the Code.
 
{bThe Code{x
The Code is a complex system of laws created by Ariakan to provide discipline
and guidance to the Knighthood, while avoiding the strict, unyielding regulations
of the Solamnic Measure. Designed to relate primarily to military situations,
the Code can also be extended into the lives of each member of the knighthood.
Strict adherance is required, although each case is considered on its own merit
and exceptions may be made. The Code is primarily concerned with the following:
 
   LOYALTY: Be known for unwavering commitment to Takhisis and the Vision. There
   are many places where compromise is expected loyalty is not amongst them.
 
   PROWESS: To seek excellence in all endeavors expected of a knight, martial and
   otherwise, seeking strength to be used in the service of the Vision, rather than
   personal aggrandizement.
 
   FAITH: A Knight must place their faith in Takhisis, for faith roots him in the
   Vision and strengthens the Blood Oath. Weakness in faith is weakness in character.
   Neither are to be tolerated.
 
   COURAGE: Being a knight means choosing the more difficult path. Be prepared to
   make personal sacrifices in service of the Takhisis and the Vision.
 
   NOBILITY: Nobility lies in service to Takhisis and the Vision. Those who perform
   well in their duty and rise above their foes shall find favor in the eyes of
   the Queen. The weak, incompetent and disloyal shall not live to regret their failures.
~

