0 'BATTLE RELIGION'~
Followers of Reorx are comprised mainly of dwarves and gnomes, both of
which consider themselves the "chosen" race of the god. The church of
Reorx is known for its stability and organization as much as for its
workmanship and invention.

The dwarven branch of Reorx's church is led by a dwarven cleric called the
Starmaster. The rest of the dwarven clergy are known as "Forgers" and
wield great influence within their clans. Blacksmiths of many races also
revere Reorx, and these devotees are expected to work from morning to
evening unless traveling (even then, the smith may take along a portable
forge) or presiding over church ceremonies.

The gnomish branch of the church does not wield as much worldly influence,
but works closely with the priesthood of Sirrion to produce much of the
necessary metals for gnomish inventions. Most gnomes serve Reorx through
the pursuit of their Life Quests.
 
Followers of Reorx may be of any combination of ethos and alignment, so
long as one or the other remains neutral. True devotees to the god of
Battle and the Forge that wish to receive a Mark of Reorx's favor must
create, during his or her lifetime, a metal object of some type that
honors Reorx. This object/invention must be made by the follower's own
hands and possess extraordinary quality or artistic value. This work can
often take years to complete.

All who follow the teachings of Reorx follow these laws of the Forge:

  ** There is beauty in creation
  ** Nothing is better in life than crafting something lasting, and the
     process is just as important as the finished product
  ** Never be idle when you can be working
  ** Tried and true methods are well and good, but innovation is vitally
     important
  ** Always strive to master your skills, honor your peers and enjoy the
     results of your work
~

0 WEALTH~
Followers of Wealth are mainly composed of merchants, mercenaries,
traders, and the occasional rogue. Some travel the land assisting
struggling business owners, serving as moneylenders, and supporting
various guilds and business ventures.

Followers of Shinare are industrious, working hard to amass wealth and
prestige, but they must not be greedy - that way lies the dark path to
Hiddukel. Rather, devotees of Wealth must work to improve the area in
which they live for the profit of the community as well as themselves.
Followers of Shinare are forbidden from being late in the payment of taxes,
tithes or other expenses, and from cheating in any way whatsoever when it
comes to matters of finance.

Devotees of Shinare are typically of Lawful or Neutral ethos, and Neutral
alignment. Those wishing to earn a sign of Shinare's favor must have
amassed a certain amount of personal wealth, and are often charged with
finding some sort of business venture in which to invest.

Those devoted to Wealth and industry live by the following code:

  ** Work hard and you will be rewarded by wealth
  ** Greed will destroy what you have worked to gain
  ** Poverty is lack of effort - never tolerate laziness
  ** Lead others in enterprise and safeguard all transactions
  ** Be fair and honest in business, for deception is the road to ruin
  ** Competition is the wellspring of all fortune
~

0 'FLAME' 'FLAME RELIGION'~
Followers of Sirrion are often passionate in nature, yet erratic and
changeable. Those who desire only power are scorned by the god, as
destruction is the realm of Sargonnas. Instead, those who follow the way
of Flame do so for its beauty and transformational qualities.

Clerics of Sirrion must tend to an ever-burning fire in their home or
temple, meditating upon it as a symbol of the inner fire of the soul. Days
are usually spent tending to communal fires such as those in smithies,
taverns, and other public places. Now and again during the evenings,
followers of Sirrion may build bonfires; causing the flames to dance and
change color in order to entertain and teach others about their own inner
fires.

Sirrion accepts followers of all alignments, though only of Chaotic ethos -
as unpredictable and ever-changing as the fire he embodies. Those wish to
be Marked by the god's Flame must teach others to respect and revere the
power and beauty of fire, and use that fire to either transform something
for the benefit of others or keep it from turning destructive (aiding in the
control and saving of forest and city fires would be an example of this).
 
Followers of Sirrion are required to live by the following flames of truth:
 
  ** Fire is life, fire is death
  ** Fire is honest and does not discriminate
  ** Fire is the instrument of change
  ** Remove the fear of fire from the people and teach them all the good
     things that fire can do for them
  ** Harness flame to bring light and warmth into the world
  ** Never allow a fire to rage out of control, for all flame that burns
     should have a purpose
  ** Seek the fire in others and in yourself
~

0 'LIFE' 'LIFE RELIGION'~
Zivilyn is often said to be the wisest of the gods. Known as the "Tree
of Life", Zivilyn teaches his followers that wisdom transcends both Good
and Evil, and is a force unto itself. Followers of Zivilyn can be found
all over Krynn, serving as counselors, mediators, philosophers and
diplomats. Occasionally, if no cleric of Paladine can be found, Zivilyn's
followers may be seen acting as legal officials or advisors in trials.

Unlike those of Gilean, followers of Zivilyn prefer to facilitate rather
than teach, encouraging others to learn through experience rather than
cloistered research and study. Recognizing that wisdom comes with age,
the highest ranks of Zivilyn's clergy are reserved for the eldest of their
order. Those who follow the Life Tree are calm and deliberate, never
making rash decisions or giving way to fits of temper. Much like the
Aesthetic order, Zivilyn's followers remain uninvolved in the struggle for
supremacy between Good and Evil, and are not swayed by impassioned pleas
or bribery of any sort.

Devotees of Zivilyn may be of any combination of ethos and alignment, so
long as at least one or the other remains Neutral. Straying from this path
may well cause the follower to be forsaken by their god. Those wishing to
be marked by the wisdom of Life are often called upon to solve one or more
tests of wisdom, or some life lesson presented in the form of a riddle
that the devotee is required to solve through the wisdom of his or her own
life experience.

All who embrace the tenets of Zivilyn live by the following Life lessons:

  ** Wisdom is timeless. Act only after you have studied all courses
     of action
  ** Be free of material influence, choose no side in war or conflict
  ** Seek understanding, not facts, for knowledge is fallible whereas
     wisdom is not
  ** All wisdom comes from within - it cannot be learned or borrowed
  ** Be an advisor to those who seek peace
  ** Be at peace with Nature, for it is the cradle of wisdom, and be at
     peace with yourself, for you are the vessel of wisdom
~

0 'DEATH RELIGION'~
Followers of Chemosh seek to undermine the works of the orders of Good,
turning mortals away from life to the mockery of life offered by their
god. Most cult members work in secret, expanding their numbers through
false promises of Immortality. In turn, this secrecy means that the church
of Chemosh has no central authority. Many clerics hold their positions for
generations, using their powers to cling to control even after death.

Devotees of Chemosh may be of any ethos, but are ALL of evil alignment.
Should they stray from this path, the individual will surely find
themselves incurring their god's wrath. Those who wish to be marked by
the Lord of Death must undertake some special task of the god's
choosing for some, this may take lifetimes to complete.

The tenets followed by worshippers of Chemosh do not necessarily reflect
the god's true views, for the beliefs he fosters are intended to dupe
mortals into his control. These tenets are as follows:

  ** The world issued from Chaos, who has no purpose or grand plan for it
  ** Mortals have no souls; the flesh is all that matters
  ** Death is a gateway to oblivion
  ** The gods of Good promise life after death to enslave their
     worshippers; service to Chemosh is rewarded with true everlasting life
~

0 'CORRUPTION' 'CORRUPTION RELIGION'~
Very few people willingly become followers of Hiddukel. Usually, the
deity tricks a person into service, at the cost of their soul. Followers
of Hiddukel are ordered to pursue and attain wealth, prestige and
influence by any means necessary, and seek to get the best of everyone in
any and all bargains. Clerics of Hiddukel operate in secret, under the
guise of legitimate concerns, and large cities are often home to hidden
cells of his worshippers.

Those who follow the god of Corruption often lead double lives, appearing
as respected members of the community by day and conducting illicit
activity by night. Hiddukel prizes treachery in his followers, even when
their treachery turns against him. Every follower works for themselves,
constantly scheming and backstabbing to gain dominance over the others.
Every year, followers of Hiddukel must present the god with a tally of
those they have either corrupted or driven into ruin. Those who fail face
the wrath of the god.

Hiddukel's followers are typically Chaotic Evil, Chaotic Neutral, or
Neutral Evil. Those wishing to obtain the mark of their god's favor must
undertake a particular quest, often involving some form of swindle or
corrupting others to betray those dear to them.

Followers of Hiddukel live by the following creed:

  ** Greed is the driving force in the world
  ** Those who deny that they love money are lying
  ** Nothing in the world is as important as wealth
  ** Acquire riches, no matter who stands in your way
  ** Lies give the truth meaning
  ** Discover someone's deepest desire and you will find
     the key to his soul
~

0 'DISEASE' 'DISEASE RELIGION'~
The church of Morgion is composed of slaves. Morgion waits until disease
seizes hold of a person, then offers respite from the disease in exchange
for life-long servitude.  Those who accept find themselves "cured", only
to be sent forth to carry disease to others; thereby gaining Morgion
more followers.

Cultists of Morgion gather in small groups, usually no more than three,
whose task is to spread disease and suffering to everyone they encounter.
This task also includes the study and creation of various poisons,
especially those that mimic the effects of disease. These cultists may be
found anywhere - large cities, small villages, even the elven lands and
as far away as the minotaur isles - but must work in secret, for if they
were discovered their lives would be forfeit. Above all, they fear their
sworn enemies; the clerics of Mishakal.

Followers of Morgion may be of any ethos, but MUST be of evil alignment.
Those wishing to receive their god's blessing must serve their god in
some remarkable way including, but not limited to: infesting cities or
decimating a village through the spread of disease and plague, poisoning
key figures in such a manner as to indicate ill-health as the culprit,
and bringing more followers into the fold. Other tasks may be assigned
at the god's discretion.

The servants of Morgion live by a simple code:

  ** Disease breeds fear
  ** Fear is power
  ** Spread disease and reap the terrible reward
~

0 'DESTRUCTION' 'DESTRUCTION RELIGION'~
The majority of those who worship Sargonnas are minotaurs, who refer to
him as Sargas and worship him above all other gods. To them, Sargas
represents power gained by strength and held through honor. Minotaurs tend
to look down on any member of another race who claims to worship Sargonnas,
and often refuse to admit that this deity is the same god as Sargas.

Most of Sargonnas' non-minotaur worshippers view the deity as a god of
vengeance. His clerics are often sought out by individuals seeking to take
unlawful revenge on those who have wronged them. Bounty hunters and
mercenaries are among the most common of Sargonnas' followers. Despite
their general attitude that might makes right, and that mercy is a sign
of weakness, most followers of Sargonnas adhere to a warrior code of
honor that respects prowess in battle, even among enemies, and looks down
upon sneaky or underhanded tactics of any sort, believing that those who
are strong need no such methods.

Those who follow the tenets of Sargonnas are typically of Lawful ethos,
and Neutral or Evil alignment - though Neutral Evil worshippers are also
accepted. Those wishing to receive the blessings of their god must prove
their might through an increasing series of challenges, usually involving
trials by combat against a series of foes.

The warrior code adhered to by the followers of Sargonnas is as follows:

  ** Strength is power - the weak have no place in society
  ** Power is gained through strength and held through honor
  ** Be loyal to those who are loyal to you - destroy those who betray you
  ** Wreak vengeance on those who wrong you
  ** Never show mercy, for mercy dishonors both you and your enemy
~

0 'STORM' 'STORM RELIGION'~
The followers of Zeboim are mainly comprised of sailors, pirates and
evil druids, although many others worship her out of fearful respect,
or in an effort to please her mother, Queen Takhisis. Priests of Zeboim
are seen as welcome additions to the crew, leading the sailors in prayer
and making offerings to the Sea Queen.

Clerics of Zeboim tend to reflect the dual nature of their goddess and
are not above resorting to extortion, frightening ship owners and sailors
into paying tithes in exchange for good weather. While on land, priests of
Zeboim take a ritual swim each morning, regardless of weather conditions.
Every eight months, under the full moon of Solinari, a ceremony known as
the Sea Queen's Share is performed. During this ceremony, the priest
sacrifices most of their wealth to the goddess by sending it forth into
the ocean. If the goddess is pleased with the sacrifice, most of the items
will float back. If not, they are never seen again.

Followers of Zeboim tend to reflect the Chaotic nature of their goddess,
and are of Neutral or Evil alignment - though Neutral Evil followers are
not unheard of. Those wishing to receive special favor from the Sea Queen
must spend long voyages in meditation and prayer (along with a generous
sacrifice), if the goddess is pleased, she may assign the devotee a
particular task according to her whim.

Followers of Zeboim live by the following code:

  ** People respect and fear fury
  ** No sailor is safe unless the Sea Queen wills it - therefore, worship
     her and offer her many gifts
  ** In time, the sea will consume all, and all lands will drown under
     the power of Zeboim - adore her or be lost to the storm
~

0 'HATRED' 'HATRED RELIGION'~
Those who worship Takhisis serve as her eyes and ears upon Krynn and obey
her without hesitation, working tirelessly to open the doorway that will
admit her into the world in her full glory. The goddess urges her followers
to seek positions of power, no matter what the cost, and her clerics are
free to use any means necessary to achieve dominance, including lying,
extortion and murder. Those who worship the Dark Queen also fear her, for
she is swift to punish those who betray her, or refuse to obey her commands.

Clerics of Takhisis are found in all parts of the world, many of them
brazenly open about their faith, though most find that they must resort to
secrecy to achieve their goals. They pass their days plotting and
manipulating; working to destroy or sabotage the power of every other
deity of Krynn. Many of her Dark Majesty's clerics are non-humans. Ogres
are her most devoted followers, though draconians also revere her deeply.

Takhisis demands the strictest obedience from her subjects, and therefore,
her followers are universally of Lawful ethos and Evil alignment. Those
followers who wish to receive the Dark Queen's blessing must undertake a
special task for the goddess, designed to advance her ambitions and
strengthen her base of power, as well as weakening that of the other gods.

Worshippers of Takhisis are united by the following strictures:

  ** Those who serve Takhisis are destined to rule the world and bring
     order out of chaos
  ** Power must be attained at any cost
  ** Trust none except for those you control
{x  ** Do not let such things as love and compassion weaken you or blind
     you to what must be done
  ** Betrayal is punished by eternal torment - Service is rewarded
     with dominion
~

