102 'EXLIST'~
Syntax: exlist
 
This command will display a list of rooms that are connected
to rooms that are in the area you are in.
 
For example: using this command in palanthas might give you something like this:
 
 3001 Entrance to the Temple of  <     2 Limbo                     (void    )
 3103 The Private Section    <> 2913 Along a Winding Passagehallknow)
 3164 On a wooden dock           <>10843 On a wooden dock          (nevermin)
 3261 Temple Row             <  9400 Before the grove          (shoikan )
 3256 Outside the Gates of Palan <>13701 High Knight's Road        (clerist )
 3260 Gates of Paladine          <> 2800 Zeboim's Deep         (zebdeep )
 3266 Nobles Way             <>13700 Inside the Solamnic Knight(clerist )
 3001 Entrance to the Temple of  <  3760 A Safe Room               (school  )
 3001 Entrance to the Temple of   > 3700 Great Doors of the Palanth(school  )
 3052 Outside the West Gate of P <>  927 Vingaard Road             (palroads)
 3053 Outside the East Gate of P <>  900 Along a dirt road         (palroads)
 
 
So, now what does this all mean? First, lets start with the first thing in the
list, which is a VNUM. That VNUM is the vnum of the room that is linked to a room
in a different area. The title following the VNUM, is the NAME of that room. The
next syntax after the name, are greater than (>) or less than (<) symbols. These
symbols represent which way the rooms are connected. But before we get into that,
we'll explain what comes after those symbols. The next thing is another VNUM. This
is the VNUM of the room which is in another area that is connected
to the room in palanthas (or the area your in) that preceeds it on the same line.
The next thing on each line, the name of an area in parenthesis, is the name of the
area in which the name of the room just prior to it, belongs to. Now that we know
what all the names are, we can discuss what those <> symbols represent.
Lets take the first one:
3001 Entrance to the Temple of  <     2 Limbo                     (void    )
 
This means that those 2 rooms are connected (VNUMS: 3001 and 2) However, they are
only connected via 1 direction. This means that if you are in room vnum 2, you can
enter the room 3001. However, you can not go the other way. Now, on the next line
you see:
3103 The Private Section    <> 2913 Along a Winding Passagehallknow)
This means that you can be in either room, and you can enter the other from one
another.
 
This is one of those "either you get it, or you don't and hence then should not use
it" commands. This command is used to help best determine which areas are linked
to what other areas, and through which rooms are they connected
by. It is used mostly for builders, and is also used when transporting over areas
from our Builder Port, in case ALL exits in a particular area,
need to be removed.
~

