1 'SING' 'SINGING' 'SONG'~
Syntax: sing <number> / stop
        song <list>
{x        song <title> <text>
{x        song <read> <number>
{x        song <+> <text>
{x        song <clear>
{x        song <show>
{x        song <pretty>
{x        song <delete> <line number>
{x        song <insert> <line number> <text>
{x        song <compose>
{x        song <remove> <song number>
{x        song <expunge>
 
A lot of commands for this special skill/command. First off, a foot note should be
inserted here, letting the Bard know that SONG and SONGS are two different commands.
Song will allow you to use this command. SONGS, will still display a list of songs
that the Bard can play, using a Musical instrument, using the PLAY skill. These 2
skills/commands should never get confused with being one and the same. They are
completely seperate and different.
 
SING <NUMBER> / STOP - This command will allows you to sing a song on your SONG
list (NOT SONGS LIST). The songs in this list are listed in numerical order. To
sing song number 4 for example, you'd type SING 4. While in the MIDDLE of singing
a song, you may choose to STOP singing for whatever reason. To do this, type
SING STOP. This will halt you from continuing with the song.
 
SONG LIST - this will display a list of songs that are available for you to
sing. This list will display the song NUMBER, which is to be used as your reference
when wanting to sing that particular song.
 
SONG TITLE <TEXT> - This will set the TITLE for a new song, which is one method to
also BEGIN writing a new song.
 
SONG READ <NUMBER> - This will read (display) the context of the song you specify.
 
SONG <+> <TEXT> - This will ADD new lines to the Song you are composing.
 
SONG CLEAR - This command will completely clear ALL text you have written for the
song you are currently editing.
 
SONG SHOW - This command will display what you have written thus far, providing
you are in the middle of editing a new song
 
SONG PRETTY - This command is VERY IMPORTANT. You MUST use this command upon
completion, BEFORE YOU COMPOSE it. If your song is *NOT* Pretty'd, the output
display people will see, may become distorted, as the code automatically displays
a certain amount of text per line, whether reading from a new line or not.
 
SONG DELETE <line number> - This will delete 1 particular line from the song you
are currently editing.
 
SONG INSERT <line number> <text> - This will insert text into
your song at the specified line number.
 
SONG COMPOSE - This will POST the song you are editing to your SONG list. This is
the final step to getting your new songs ready for use. Without using this command,
your song will NOT be posted.
 
SONG REMOVE <number> - This will remove a song from your list, specified by which
number the song is on your list that you input.
 
SONG EXPUNGE <number> This is for IMPLEMENTORS ONLY!! This will remove any song
from the list that you specify.
 
** If you are unsure about how to use these commands, sit back, take a deep breath,
relax, and try again but more slowly. Do NOT try rushing this command as if you
were a master at it, until you feel more comfortable. Like anything else, this
new skill/command works as described here in the HELP file, not how your twisted
mind may think it should work. ;)
 
 
*** Also, if you wish to have each sentence you sing on a new line, you
need only add in a PERIOD.  Regardless of how the SONG PRETTY command
actually formats your song, adding in a period will ensure that the next set
of words go onto a NEW line.
~

