Autodig is a command that can be toggled on and off. When this command is
active and the person is in REDIT, a builder can enter in any direction
(N, S, E, W, U, D) and autodig will do several things automatically: it
will generate a new room in that direction; it will create a two-way link
between the existing room and the new room; it will move the builder into
the new room; and the new room will have the very next available VNUM
numerically.
{x
Example: you are editing room 5200. By turning autodig on and entering
"North", room 5201 will be created automatically, and you will be moved
there. There will be a single exit in room 5201, and it will lead South,
to room 5200.
