Now, continuing to use the above example, say you want to move to the South,
to get back to room 5200.  You will need to ensure that you've exited out of
autodig FIRST! By typing South with autodig active, simply moving to the
room is not what will happen. Instead, autodig will create another room to
the south of 5201 that has the VNUM 5202. You will then have a case of two
rooms overlapping, and while this will not crash the game, it will make your
area messy and unplayable. Because of this, not being mindful of when autodig
is active or inactive can lead to a long span of time disconnecting and
reconnecting rooms in the right order.
